rd.com/uryaeldaggerfall.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ryael Daggerfall</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ninja Looter</span><br>  Posts: 36<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/20/02 3:11:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2167.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> How far can you push the envelope?</span><hr size=1> There have been plenty of threads that focus on this particular topic; can characters on opposite sides of the law join together? And if so, to what extent, and is there a requirement for a &quot;reason&quot; ?<br>
<br>
My personal opinion (and this relates moreso to the ruleset of the server, and perhaps the 'RP enforcement' thread posted earlier) is that you can and should roleplay accurately -- meaning, no Dark Elves and Wood Elves fighting the good fight, hand in hand -- if at all possible, but I don't think that it should be a mortal sin if you want to play the game with friends of opposing race / class.<br>
<br>
I love roleplaying, and I love EverQuest -- but sometimes the limitations of the game don't make for the best RP experience. Yeah, go to a blue server if you want to be the best d00d in town with a set of Ravenscale armor at level 3 1/2, come to Firiona Vie if you want to roleplay; I know this. I'm not going to walk around and disrupt roleplayers with inane chitchat, but it's not a felony to /tell someone without the (OOC) tag, or to speak OOC in an isolated area with someone else. I also think that it's not that big of a deal to group with someone you personally wouldn't, if you were your character. If you find offense to this last comment, though, I have this to say; what does it really matter what other people do as long as it doesn't affect you even in the slightest bit? RPer or not, we're all human beings with personal lives, and in our spare time, should we want to play EQ (and we usually do), why do we have to be bound by unwritten laws that prohibit even the tiniest gesture of non-roleplay? In contradiction to my previous statement, say that a Dark Elf and a Wood Elf grouped together and went around fighting monsters. Who's the victim?<br>
<br>
Yeah, like I said, FV is the roleplay server; but there are more reasons than that to come here. It's not as crowded as other servers, there's a lot less twinking, and the economy is still better than the alternative(s). And yes, like I said, roleplay should be encouraged -- but just that, encouraged. It's an RP preferred server. And it's that for a reason.<br>
<br>
I guess my point is (as incoherent as it may seem) that there's a time for roleplay and a time where it doesn't really matter. If you're around people that are roleplaying, for God's sake, don't kill it with OOC. If you aren't, who cares? Given the choice, I'd rather RP; but people who verbally assault those who aren't as uber- and dedicated to the pastime as they are should think about this. Or not, I don't care. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uryaeldaggerfall.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ryael Daggerfall</A> at: 6/20/02 3:24:23 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uryaeldaggerfall.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ryael Daggerfall</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ninja Looter</span><br>  Posts: 37<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/20/02 3:35:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2167.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How far can you push the envelope?</span><hr size=1> And by the way, in case you're up for changing my mind, I'm willing to listen provided that your response isn't just telling me how stupid I am. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/udorphen01.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dorphen 01</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/20/02 3:42:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2167.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How far can you push the envelope?</span><hr size=1> <br>
